SIMPLE: nibble
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nibble
<hw>Nib"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Nibbled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Nibbling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Nip</er>.]</ety> <def>To bite by little at a time; to seize gently
with the mouth; to eat slowly or in small bits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy turfy mountains, where live <qex>nibbling</qex> sheep.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nibble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nibble
<hw>Nib"ble</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To bite upon something gently or
cautiously; to eat a little of a thing, as by taking small bits
cautiously; <as>as, fishes <ex>nibble</ex> at the bait</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Instead of returning a full answer to my book, he manifestly falls
a-<qex>nibbling</qex> at one single passage.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nibble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: nibble
<hw>nib"ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small or cautious
bite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>(Fig.)</mark> <def>An
expression of interest, often tentative, as at the beginning of a sale
or negotiation process.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nibbler</ent>⟦br⟧
